# Build context for all deploy/* Dockerfiles is the repo ROOT (the pnpm workspace).
# This file keeps that context small: drop installed deps, native/build artifacts,
# the private docs, and the heavy mobile/demo apps that no deployable service needs.
# pnpm's `--filter "<pkg>..."` selects the real dependency subtree at build time, so
# excluding unrelated apps here only shrinks the upload — it never removes a dep a
# server-side service actually pulls in (apps → packages, never the reverse).

**/node_modules
**/.git
.git

# native / mobile build outputs (hundreds of MB each)
**/android
**/ios
**/.gradle
**/.expo
**/build
**/dist
**/*.apk
**/*.aab
**/*.keystore

# private / local-only docs + scratch (never ship)
plans
_archive
outreach
.obsidian
session-notes
test-results
test-results/**
playwright-report
.vercel
**/*.log

# real secrets — only .env.example templates ship
**/.env
**/.env.*
!**/.env.example

# heavy mobile + demo + web apps (not part of any deployable backend service)
apps/canopy-chat-mobile
apps/folio-mobile
apps/stoop-mobile
apps/tasks-mobile
apps/sdk-smoke
apps/mesh-demo
apps/website
apps/website-publiek
